Answer.comment: The instructions are even more difficult to understand than the previous round. The definitions for each criteria are far too convoluted and you're asking too much of workers to keep scrolling back and forth to make sure they've got the right one (there's no way we're memorizing over 30 different criteria that differ only slightly, I hope you understand why this is not reasonable to ask over a mere 5 HITs for 67 cents). Honestly, this is ridiculous, and if you expect perfect compliance, the pay rate has to be MUCH better than this, or you should only be asking ONE criteria at a time. Not 3 different ones with 10 different variations each.
